                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract1489-1">Sophia or "wisdom"
                        with her three daughters, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2016"
                            >Faith</persName>, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1707"
                            >Hope</persName>, and <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1563"
                            >Charity</persName>, were martyred in Rome under Hadrian. Sophia was
                        invoked as a saint to fight malaria.</note>
